### 1. Chain 01

Best ceiling in the portfolio. It has the most theorem-shaped success mode and the most disciplined obstruction taxonomy.

### 2. Chain 02

Best direct test of whether exact NS interaction geometry contains a Tao-sensitive gain. It is narrow enough to audit cleanly and still valuable if the answer is negative.

### 3. Chain 03

Best pressure-adjacent route still alive after earlier eliminations. It engages the central stretching bottleneck directly and should still return a useful non-coercivity diagnosis if it fails.

### 4. Chain 04

Most concrete geometry variant, but also the most vulnerable to persistence and nonlocal-debt failure before earning a portable theorem gap or criterion-scale output.

